cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the planning process for the evolution of cellular networks, which involves the optimization of network infrastructure and resource sharing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the constraints imposed by competition regulation, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of a framework to model the planning process suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of competition regulation on the deployment of next-generation technologies, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
